title: ∙ The Frankens said that his rule was more important than that of the founders?
subtitle: Senator Al Franken confirmed that his vote in Parliament would be separated from the results of the Minnesota groupings but did not specifically suggest that his ruling was "more important" than his constituents wanted.
author: Kim LaCapria
vclaim: Senator Al Franken told a CNN interviewer that his sentence as Superdelgate was more important than that of the constituency.
